---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About | Adam Penn" description="The founder story: from software engineering to real estate, investing, and building for freedom.">
  <div class="container">

    <div class="page-header animate-in delay-1">
      <h1>About</h1>
    </div>

    <!-- Bio with photo -->
    <section class="section animate-in delay-2">
      <div class="bio-section">
        <img src="/headshot.jpg" alt="Adam Penn" class="bio-photo" />
        <div class="bio-text">
          <p>
            I'm Adam Penn, a founder, operator, and investor based in Northern California.
            I build businesses around real assets and run them with an engineering mindset:
            systems-first, data-driven, and built to last.
          </p>
          <p>
            I run <a href="https://bidwellcapitalfund.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bidwell Capital Fund</a>,
            <a href="https://pennproperties.us" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Penn Properties</a>,
            and co-host the <a href="http://wealthindependencepod.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Wealth Independence Podcast</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Longer bio -->
    <section class="section animate-in delay-3">
      <span class="section-label">The Longer Version</span>
      <div style="max-width: 560px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem;">
        <p>
          I studied Computer Science and started my career as a software engineer in Northern California.
          I enjoyed the craft: solving problems, building systems, shipping code. But somewhere along the way,
          I started to feel the pull toward something more tangible. I wanted to build things I could see
          and touch, not just deploy.
        </p>
        <p>
          In 2017, I put $23,000 into my first short-term rental. I figured if I could debug software
          systems, I could figure out real estate operations. It turned out to be true, and more
          interesting than I expected. I used strategic debt and reinvested every gain. That one
          property became two, then five, then a $1.6 million portfolio, then a management company,
          then a fund.
        </p>
        <p>
          Today I manage 35+ rental units through Penn Properties, where I handle
          everything from guest experience to maintenance systems to revenue optimization.
          On the investment side, Bidwell Capital Fund helps other investors access real asset strategies:
          short-term rental funds, oil syndications, and tax-advantaged structures.
        </p>
        <p>
          The podcast started because I kept having the same conversations with friends in tech
          who wanted to invest but didn't know where to start beyond index funds.
          Dustin Bailey and I created Wealth Independence to share real frameworks,
          real case studies, and honest conversations about building passive income.
        </p>
        <p>
          The common thread across everything I do is simple: I believe in owning real assets,
          running disciplined operations, and building toward a life where your work and your
          freedom aren't in conflict. That's the game I'm playing.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- How I think -->
    <section class="section animate-in delay-4">
      <span class="section-label">How I Think</span>
      <ul class="principles-list">
        <li>I approach investing like an engineer: test the hypothesis, measure the result, iterate.</li>
        <li>I'd rather own fewer things well than many things poorly.</li>
        <li>Operations are the moat. Anyone can buy an asset; not everyone can run it.</li>
        <li>I optimize for autonomy, not status.</li>
        <li>I'm skeptical of complexity. The best systems are simple enough to survive stress.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

  </div>
</Base>
